annotation.TEXT: Oh, it's a case of multiple identical rooms in a row.
I hope I didn't miss any trinkets today. There's 5 left in the whole level, and I'll certainly want them all. Alright, so next time, I'll be resuming my trek through this Bizarro World!
Oh, there we go! I had enough time to dodge the squares by quickly flipping again after veering right slightly.
Ow, my other big toe!
Oh, and since last time, I've corrected my death count and gameplay time to what they should be: 284 deaths, and 1:16:18.
Ow, my big toe!
destx = 14, and desty = 1? Sounds like coordinates (14,1). Is that where the Polar Dimension is?
To be continued... Yo!
Okay, I'm suddenly one room to the left of where I just was, and now "ecroF evitisoP" is playing...
Polar Dimension? Am I going to have to make a Katamari exactly 10 meters in diameter there? (I can actually do that consistently now.)
Ow, my Skechers!
Ow, my Square One Squares!
What the heck happened there? I died, and then warped, but the warp didn't work right and I just died again. That was weird.
Whoa, what the heck?
I'll try the Tap Tap the Red Nose strategy now.
Okay, now just time this right...
Well, that's not good... Valso suddenly vanished! He didn't happen to mention Candlejack earlier, did he? So, is it too late to restabilize this dimen
Heh. Tiny shortcut FTW.
D'oh! Is there not enough time to quickly flip to avoid the squares? Will I actually need to make that pinpoint landing on the edge of the ledge above?
Okay, and how long have I been playing so far today?
Oh, come on! I'm certain I didn't tap the left arrow key any more than usual there! This is really aggravating me now!
Okay, so where am I now?
Nope. That doesn't work. I was hoping the squares would turn around before hitting the end of that corridor.
Ow, my Thad Green!
Ow, my knee cap! It begins... Should I speed this up and put on Yakety Sax?
Ow, my face! Wow, did this game suddenly turn into Syobon/Eryi's Action or something?
Ow, my Adidas!
Ack! That failed. However, I might be able to land there with pinpoint accuracy.
Yep. Oh, but I'm suspicious of something...
Oh, man. It can't be nearly as bad as the Turbo Tunnel in Battletoads, right?
D'oh. A square got stuck in the floor down there. That's gonna complicate things.
Whoa, that's a lot of rings... Also, I see a shiny, but I can't reach it from here.
Ow, my Levi's!
Somehow made it that time, and it was all for a Death Trap... Well, now I know. Okay, so back through the Lost rooms I go.
Yeah, apparently, it's the destabilizing of this dimension that's caused almost everyone to vanish.
Oh, man! I'm so glad I wasn't hugging the right wall as I fell there!
About 9 minutes. Hmm... yeah, I think I'll end this episode now, before something else has a chance to annoy me greatly. Oh, and I had 42 deaths today, BTW.
Agh! So close!
Alright, that square is now free! Now, let's try to complete this room. I honestly think my best bet is to try to land where the trinket was again.
Uh, huh...
Whoa, what?!
Man, the colored terrain down there is playing tricks on my eyes now, doing that optical illusion thing where they don't actually look parallel to each other.
Okay, I gotta remember that this trinket is in room (19,1), and I have to approach the room from below.
Alright, let's head towards the emerald keycard gate, through this annoyingly tricky passage that I'm sure is going to kill me a lot again.
Whoa, I got multiplied by myself before I could react there.
Last time, I had acquired the emerald keycard and made my way to this passage that leads to the emerald keycard gate.
So, now I'm down there. Wait, what if I go back to the right now?
Change "dissappearences" to "disappearances" here. (Remove one of the first two "s"s, and change "ences" at the end to "ances".)
Oh, what? The Root Beer Slushie Tapper Slinger strategy didn't work there? Maybe I just didn't tap properly that time.
Whoa, that's a lot of squares. Also, I see a shiny!
Ow, my David Numberman!
I guess I weave my way through the top and then head back to the left, where I'll probably land at that checkpoint down there... maybe.
Made it!
Excellent! No deaths in that very short Hi-Speed Warp Tunnel!
Too bad I can't simply leave and reenter the room to reset everything. I'm going to see if I can free that one square down there...
Shine get! That wasn't so hard. But, getting out of here might be tricky...
Well, whether this is the Polar Dimension or not, I am indeed at (14,1) right now.
Hey there, Valso! What's up?
Oh, geez. Was I just whisked away as well?
Change "suprise" to "surprise" here.
Yoink! Okay, now I should technically be in a different room, so I should head left now, I think.
Oh, man. Talk about a cleverly hidden trinket! I wonder if I would've found this one without the assistance of the map...
Okay, there's obviously a surprise coming... It even says so, with a misspelled word.
I like how this room is called Found.
Ow, my Joe Greco!
Alright, let's unlock this gate!
Thanks, vanishing platforms, for vanishing after my previous death.

Oh, hey! I do believe that's Valso down there! Yeah, last time, something happened that caused most of the V-people to disappear, and I was told by Verisix before he vanished to find Valso, who hadn't vanished yet.
Ow, my toenails!
Or, I guess I head right, after doing a wraparound.
Argh, now this is gonna get annoying, isn't it?
Bah! It got me... Kogasa would be proud.
Okay, "received" is spelled right here. (main_gi, was this "received" spelled correctly in the previous version as well?)
Okay, made it that time. There's a checkpoint somewhere nearby, right?
Okay, this is getting absurd. This shouldn't be that difficult, really.
Actually, I believe this is where the map is meant to be disabled, but since the map doesn't turn on again after finishing this area, main_gi made it so that the map never turns off in this version.
Hmm... Well, this place certainly seems unstable.
Okay, what trick is the game gonna pull on me here?
Oh, but... I don't want to hit that checkpoint yet, because there's a path back in "We Deployed It Early" that I didn't check. So, I'm going to intentionally die to go back there.
Whoa. Okay, this game's really trying to get to me with its mind... games... mind... games...
Huh. Suddenly, my position has shifted downward, and I'm no longer making any rightward progress, so I should probably try going left now.
Whoa, what? Alright, well... I guess Yakety Sax won't be necessary, since I only died once in this passage this time!
Yep. I wish the tapping strategy hadn't failed me back in "We Deployed It Early", because now I'm in an annoyed mindset.

Hello, and welcome back to VVVVVV on this fine Friday the 13th! Let's resume Dimension Open, which main_gi sent me an update for, which I guess fixes certain things, such as a few typos and a broken teleporter.
